-shah-rukh-khan-plants-a-kiss-on-javed-jaaferis-daughters-forehead-at-anant-ambanis-pre-wedding-festivities-me-when%2Farticleshow%2F108254428.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Williamson%20Clarifies%20As%20Ross%20Taylor%20Calls%20Wagner's%20Retirement%20'Forced'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EFormer%20New%20Zealand%20batter%20Ross%20Taylor%20has%20said%20that%20the%20retirement%20of%20pacer%20Neil%20Wagner%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bforced%26quot%3B%20one.%20Ahead%20of%20the%20first%20Test%20between%20Australia%20and%20New%20Zealand%2C%20Kiwi%20fast%20bowler%20Wagner%20had%20announced%20his%20retirement%20from%20international%20cricket.%20The%2037-year-old%20pacer%20took%20the%20emotional%20choice%20after%20a%20difficult%20chat%20with%20coach%20Gary%20Stead%20during%20which%20it%20was%20made%20clear%20that%20he%20was%20not%20in%20New%20Zealand's%20top%20XI%20for%20the%20forthcoming%20series%20against%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20left-armer%20finished%20his%20Test%20career%20fifth%20overall%20on%20the%20list%20of%20New%20Zealand%20Test%20wicket-takers%2C%20with%20260%20scalps%20in%2064%20Tests.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it%20all%20makes%20sense%20a%20little%20bit%20now.%20There%20is%20no%20sugarcoating%20it%3A%20I%20think%20it%20is%20a%20forced%20retirement.%20If%20you%20listen%20to%20Wagner's%20press%20conference%2C%20he%20was%20retiring%2C%20but%20it%20was%20after%20this%20last%20Test%20match%20%5Bagainst%20Australia%5D.%20So%20he%20did%20make%20himself%20available%2C%26quot%3B%20Taylor%20said%20on%20Tuesday%20as%20quoted%20by%20ESPNCricinfo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20responding%20to%20a%20question%20on%20ESPN's%20'Around%20the%20Wicket'%20podcast%20about%20Wagner's%20finger-on-the-mouth%20celebration%20during%20the%20second%20Test%20against%20South%20Africa%20held%20earlier%20in%20February%2C%20which%20was%20his%20last%20Test%20appearance%20and%20a%20visual%20of%20him%20making%20explicit%20gestures%20as%20the%20team%20got%20into%20a%20huddle%20to%20celebrate%20a%20dismissal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20first%20Test%2C%20Wagner%20did%20make%20an%20appearance%20as%20a%20substitute%20fielder%20and%20carried%20drinks%20for%20his%20teammates.%20Wagner%20was%20set%20to%20be%20released%20from%20the%20team%20after%20the%20first%20Test%2C%20but%20William%20O'Rourke's%20injury%20presented%20an%20opportunity%20of%20a%20potential%20recall%20during%20the%20second%20Test%20at%20Christchurch.%20Kiwis%20chose%20to%20go%20with%20uncapped%20pacer%20Ben%20Sears%20over%20Wagner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaylor%20further%20said%20that%20though%20the%20team%20has%20to%20look%20out%20and%20plan%20for%20its%20future%2C%20but%20a%20Test%20against%20Trans-Tasman%20rivals%20Australia%2C%20that%20too%20a%20must-win%20match%2C%20called%20for%20Wagner's%20inclusion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20to%20see%20that%20he%20is%20not%20selected...%20I%20think%20you%20do%20need%20to%20plan%20for%20the%20future%2C%20but%20a%20one-off%20Test%20against%20Australia%20in%20a%20must-win%20situation%2C%20I%20would%20not%20be%20looking%20much%20further%20than%20Neil%20Wagner.%20And%20I%20am%20sure%20the%20Australian%20batters%20are%20sleeping%20easy%20that%20he%20is%20not%20in%20the%20side%2C%26quot%3B%20Taylor%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20Australian%20captain%20Aaron%20Finrch%20also%20agreed%20that%20Wagner%20could%20have%20stopped%20the%20final%20wicket-century%20partnership%20between%20Cameron%20Green%20and%20Josh%20Hazlewood%20had%20he%20been%20playing%20the%20first%20Test.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20could%20not%20believe%20Neil%20Wagner%20was%20not%20in%20the%20XI.%20I%20just%20genuinely%20thought%20that%20he%20must%20have%20been%20out%20through%20a%20niggle.%20The%20success%20he's%20had%20against%20Australia%2C%20particularly%20%5Bagainst%5D%20Steven%20Smith%20over%20a%20period%20of%20time%2C%20you%20can%20guarantee%20that%20the%20last%20wicket%20partnership%20would%20not%20have%20happened%20if%20Wagner%20was%20there%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Finch.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBecause%20he%20would%20have%20intimidated%20Josh%20Hazlewood%20at%20least.%20He%20might%20have%20stopped%20Cameron%20Green%20from%20scoring%20as%20well.%20I%20thought%20that%20was%20a%20really%20interesting%20decision%2C%26quot%3B%20Finch%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20Kiwi%20batter%20Kane%20Williamson%20during%20a%20press%20conference%20played%20down%20all%20the%20concerns%20about%20Wagner's%20retirement%2C%20saying%20that%20%26quot%3Bnobody%20is%20forced%20to%20retire%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20ahead%20of%20the%20second%20Test%20against%20Australia%2C%20a%20must-win%20match%20starting%20from%20Friday%2C%20Williamson%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20do%20not%20think%20anybody%20is%20forced%20to%20retire.%20I%20think%20last%20week%2C%20he%20had%20a%20fantastic%20week%20and%20it%20was%20reflecting%20on%20what%20was%20an%20incredible%20career.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20had%20some%20amazing%20moments%20in%20the%20dressing%20room.%20It%20did%20not%20go%20perfectly.%20Obviously%2C%20an%20on-field%20performance%20would%20have%20helped%20but%20it%20was%20so%20much%20more%20than%20that.%20He%20has%20just%20done%20such%20incredible%20things%20for%20this%20team.%20And%20we%20have%20seen%20the%20skill%20that%20he%20has%20and%20the%20numbers%20that%20everybody%20sees%20but%20the%20heart%20and%20soul%20and%20effort%20that%20he%20has%20brought%20to%20the%20side%20and%20largely%20led%20through%20that%20for%20so%20long%20has%20been%20incredible.%20It%20was%20quite%20a%20special%20week%20for%20that%20reason%20and%20I%20think%20he%20had%20a%20really%20amazing%20time%20sharing%20that%20with%20the%20side%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWilliamson%20also%20provided%20context%20to%20Wagner's%20celebration%2C%20suggesting%20that%20it%20was%20borne%20out%20of%20some%20on-field%20banter%20between%20him%20and%20skipper%20Southee%20on%20his%20fielding.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20guys%20are%20great%20mates%20and%20have%20been%20and%20will%20continue%20to%20be.%20That%20was%20banter%20in%20the%20dressing%20room%20with%20Waggy%20and%20his%20fielding%20so%20he%20ended%20up%20putting%20him%20down%20at%20fine%20leg.%20So%20to%20get%20a%20catch%20was%20quite%20amusing.%20So%20Waggy%20took%20his%20opportunity.%20I%20think%20he%20thinks%20that%20obviously%20out%20of%20context%20%5Band%5D%20it%20does%20not%20look%20great%2C%20but%20it%20was%20a%20little%20bit%20humorous%20at%20the%20time%20and%20all%20the%20players%20understood%20the%20context%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20cleared%20all%20the%20air%20on%20the%20team's%20environment%2C%20saying%20that%20despite%20all%20the%20external%20noise%2C%20everything%20was%20fine%20within%20the%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYeah%2C%20quite%20good%20(the%20team's%20environment).%20Something%20that%20we%20are%20always%20trying%20to%20improve%20and%20evolve%20as%20a%20team.%20And%20it%20is%20something%20we%20have%20tried%20to%20do%20for%20years.%20You%20always%20have%20different%20transitions%20and%20players%20come%20and%20go%2C%20support%20staff%20come%20and%20go.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%5BTaylor%5D%20might%20know%20more%20than%20me%2C%20I%20am%20not%20sure.%20But%20I%20see%20guys%20that%20are%20giving%20everything%2C%20trying%20to%20get%20better%20as%20a%20team%2C%20trying%20to%20move%20the%20team%20forward%20and%20that%20is%20really%20a%20focus%20for%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20concluded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENew%20Zealand%20is%201-0%20down%20in%20the%20series.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Zealand%20squad%20for%20the%20second%20Test%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ETim%20Southee%20(c)%2C%20Tom%20Blundell%20(wk)%2C%20Matt%20Henry%2C%20Scott%20Kuggeleijn%2C%20Tom%20Latham%2C%20Daryl%20Mitchell%2C%20Henry%20Nicholls%2C%20Glenn%20Phillips%2C%20Rachin%20Ravindra%2C%20Mitchell%20Santner%2C%20Ben%20Sears%2C%2