r%20to%20remove%20if%20necessary%2C%20he%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20if%20the%20curtains%20took%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgeoengineering-methods-climate-change-2018-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eunexpected%20toll%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20local%20environment%2C%20they%20could%20be%20taken%20out%20and%20redesigned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAny%20intervention%20should%20be%20something%20that%20you%20can%20revert%20if%20you%20have%20second%20thoughts%2C%26quot%3B%20Moore%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Moore%20and%20his%20colleagues%20are%20still%20decades%20away%20from%20implementing%20this%20technology%20to%20save%20the%20Thwaites%2C%20they%20are%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20testing%20prototypes%20on%20a%20smaller%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20%2450%20billion%20idea%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMoore's%20colleagues%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Cambridge%20are%20already%20in%20the%20very%20early%20stages%20of%20developing%20and%20testing%20a%20prototype%2C%20and%20they%20could%20progress%20to%20the%20next%20stage%20as%20early%20as%20summer%202025%2C%20according%20to%20Moore.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20now%2C%20researchers%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Cambridge%20are%20testing%20a%203-foot-long%20version%20of%20this%20technology%20inside%20tanks.%20Once%20they've%20proven%20its%20functionality%2C%20they'll%20move%20on%20to%20testing%20it%20in%20the%20River%20Cam%2C%20either%20by%20installing%20it%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20river%20or%20by%20pulling%20it%20behind%20a%20boat%2C%20Moore%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22River%20Cam%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F57ab3062dd08955a1e8b4623%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20River%20Cam%2C%20where%20University%20of%20Cambridge%20researchers%20plan%20to%20test%20their%20Sea%20Curtains%20prototype.%3Cp%3EPremier%20Photo%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20is%20to%20gradually%20scale%20up%20the%20prototypes%20until%20evidence%20suggests%20the%20technology%20is%20stable%20enough%20to%20install%20in%20the%20Antarctic%2C%20Moore%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20all%20goes%20well%2C%20they%20could%20be%20testing%20a%20set%20of%2033-foot-long%20curtain%20prototypes%20in%20a%20Norwegian%20fjord%20in%20about%20two%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20know%2C%20what%20could%20possibly%20go%20wrong%3F%20And%20if%20there's%20no%20solution%20for%20it%2C%20then%20in%20the%20end%20you%20just%20have%20to%20give%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Moore%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20there's%20also%20a%20lot%20of%20incentive%20to%20try%20and%20make%20it%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20scaling%20comes%20an%20increased%20need%20for%20funding.%20This%20year's%20experiments%20will%20cost%20around%20%2410%2C000.%20But%20to%20get%20to%20the%20point%20where%20Moore%20and%20his%20colleagues%20could%20confidently%20implement%20this%20technology%2C%20they'll%20need%20about%20%2410%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20they%20would%20need%20another%20%2450%20billion%20to%20actually%20install%20curtains%20in%20the%20Amundsen%20Sea.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20sounds%20like%20a%20hell%20of%20a%20lot%2C%26quot%3B%20Moore%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20compare%20the%20risk-risk%3A%20the%20cost%20of%20sea%20level%20protection%20around%20the%20world%2C%20just%20coastal%20defenses%2C%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20about%20%2450%20billion%20per%20year%20per%20meter%20of%20sea%20level%20rise.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221926%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22map%20of%20sea%20level%20rise%20in%20NYC%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e78bafce7f1785b2e69aea%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221299%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThis%20map%20shows%20the%20amount%20of%20area%20in%20and%20around%20New%20York%20City%20that%20would%20become%20submerged%20if%20sea%20levels%20rose%20three%20feet%20(in%20red).%3Cp%3EClimate%20Central%20%2F%20Google%20Earth%20Engine%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20coastal%20cities%2C%20like%20New%20York%2C%20have%20the%20budget%20to%20adapt%20to%20rising%20seas%2C%20others%20won't%20even%20come%20close.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20great%20driving%20forces%20for%20us%20is%20this%20social%20justice%20point%20%E2%80%94%20that%20it's%20a%20much%20more%20equitable%20way%20of%20dealing%20with%20sea%20level%20rise%20than%20just%20saying%2C%20'We%20should%20be%20spending%20this%20money%20on%20adaptation%2C'%26quot%3B%20Moore%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20race%20against%20time%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC3018516%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EData%20shows%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20Thwaites%20glacier%2C%20and%20others%20like%20it%2C%20are%20melting%20at%20unprecedented%20rates%20due%20to%20climate%20change.%20But%20the%20question%20of%20when%20they%20could%20collapse%20remains%20up%20for%20debate%20among%20glaciologists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20really%20don't%20know%20if%20%5Bthe%20Thwaites%5D%20could%20collapse%20tomorrow%2C%20or%2010%20years%20from%20now%2C%20or%2050%20years%20from%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Moore.%20Adding%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20need%20to%20collect%20better%20data.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22320%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22thwaites%20glacier%20and%20pine%20island%20glacier%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5f60f28657b7da001ee11b23%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22377%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESatellite%20imagery%20shows%20the%20extent%20of%20damage%20to%20the%20Thwaites%20and%20Pine%20Island%20glaciers%2C%20and%20the%20tearing%20apart%20of%20their%20shear%20zones.%3Cp%3ELhermitte%20et%20al%2FPNAS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20collecting%20better%20data%20will%20take%20time%20that%20these%20glaciers%20might%20not%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProponents%20of%20glacial%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgeoengineering-technology-could-cool-the-planet-2017-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egeoengineering%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%20Moore%2C%20believe%20that%20the%20time%20for%20intervention%20is%20now.%20Other%20experts%20disagree%2C%20arguing%20that%20cutting%20carbon%20emissions%20is%20the%20only%20viable%20way%20to%20slow%20glacial%20melting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20reducing%20emissions%20is%20essential%20for%20mitigating%20the%20effects%20of%20climate%20change%2C%20Moore%20isn't%20confident%20that%20we'll%20cut%20back%20drastically%20or%20quickly%20enough%20to%20save%20the%20Thwaites.%20Once%20it%20reaches%20a%20tipping%20point%2C%20%26quot%3BThen%20the%20glacier%20doesn't%20really%20care%20anymore%20about%20what%20humans%20want%20to%20do%20about%20their%20emissions%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20that%20point%2C%20that's%20when%20you%20need%20these%20other%20tools%20in%20the%20box.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fantarctica-thwaites-doomsday-glacier-melting-collapse-flooding-curtains-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709679718000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65e7a4a190413ab8e1d98d8d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fantarctica-thwaites-doomsday-glacier-melting-collapse-flooding-curtains-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Thwaites%20glacier%20is%20melting.%20Scientists%20will%20test%20underwater%20curtains%20to%20prevent%20the%20'doomsday'%20glacier's%20total%20collapse%20and%20subsequent%20flooding.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Ellyn%20Lapointe)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A156%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fantarctica-thwaites-