.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fkirsten-dunst-spider-man-set-called-girly-girl-1235930675%2Famp%2F%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2024%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fkirsten-dunst-spider-man-set-called-girly-girl-1235930675%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Arjun%20Modhwadia%3A%20Faith%20in%20PM%20Modi%20led%20to%20BJP%20switch%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709671842000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108246614%2Cimgsize-867087.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fahmedabad%2Farjun-modhwadia-faith-in-pm-modi-led-to-bjp-switch%2Farticleshow%2F108246606.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TNN%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fahmedabad%2Farjun-modhwadia-faith-in-pm-modi-led-to-bjp-switch%2Farticleshow%2F108246606.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Saibaba%20Acquittal%3A%20From%20Lack%20of%20Sanction%20to%20Dodgy%20Evidence%2C%20High%20Court%20Judgment%20Tears%20Into%20State's%20Case%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F05%2Fsai2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMumbai%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20In%20its%20detailed%20judgment%20acquitting%20former%20Delhi%20University%20professor%20G.N.%20Saibaba%20and%20five%20others%20of%20%E2%80%98terrorism%E2%80%99%20charges%2C%20the%20Nagpur%20bench%20of%20the%20Bombay%20high%20court%20has%20virtually%20shredded%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20case%20against%20the%20six%20to%20pieces.%20Noting%20that%20fatal%20violations%20occurred%20in%20the%20manner%20in%20which%20sanction%20to%20prosecute%20was%20granted%20%E2%80%93%20a%20key%20statutory%20safeguard%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20otherwise%20draconian%20terrorism%C2%A0%20law%20%E2%80%93%20the%20court%20also%20rejected%20key%20claims%20made%20by%20the%20prosecution%20in%20the%20case%2C%20noting%20that%20they%20were%20not%20supported%20by%20evidence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20293-%20page%20judgment%20which%20describes%20the%20trial%20court%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98guilty%E2%80%99%20verdict%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cfailure%20of%20justice%E2%80%9D%20was%20uploaded%20by%20the%20court%20on%20the%20evening%20of%20March%205.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20before%20the%20judgment%20copy%20was%20made%20available%20to%20the%20state%2C%20they%20had%20moved%20a%20Special%20Leave%20Petition%20(SLP)%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20challenging%20the%20HC%E2%80%99s%20verdict.%20The%20state%20also%20sought%20a%20stay%20on%20the%20HC%E2%80%99s%20order%20but%20the%20application%20was%20instantly%20rejected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20in%20the%20day%2C%20Justice%20Vinay%20G.%20Joshi%20and%20Justice%20Valimiki%20S.%20Menezes%20acquitted%20Saibaba%2C%20along%20with%20journalist%20Prashant%20Rahi%2C%20Mahesh%20Tikri%2C%20Hem%20Keshwdatta%20Mishra%20and%20Vijay%20Nan%20Tikri%20of%20all%20charges.%20The%20sixth%20person%20in%20the%20case%2C%20Pandu%20Narote%2C%20died%20in%20August%202022%2C%20awaiting%20this%20verdict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%20claimed%20the%20accused%20were%20members%20of%20the%20banned%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20(Maoist)%20and%20charged%20them%20under%20various%20sections%20of%20the%20Unlawful%20Activities%20(Prevention)%20Act%20(UAPA).%20In%202017%2C%20the%20trial%20court%20convicted%20the%20six%20and%20sentenced%20Saibaba%20and%20five%20others%20to%20life%2C%20only%20Vijay%20Tikri%20was%20handed%20down%2010%20year%20sentence.%20Most%20of%20them%20have%20spent%20nearly%20a%20decade%20behind%20bars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UAPA%20mandates%20a%20two-layered%20sanction%20process%20before%20a%20court%20can%20put%20a%20person%20on%20trial.%20This%20involves%20clearance%20from%20an%20%E2%80%9Cindependent%E2%80%9D%20authority%20as%20well%20as%20the%20sanctioning%20authority.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESaibaba%20was%20the%20sixth%20and%20last%20person%20to%20be%20arrested%20in%20the%20case.%20The%20trial%20court%20framed%20charges%20under%20UAPA%20against%20Saibaba%20on%20February%2021%2C%202015%20even%20though%20the%20order%20sanctioning%20his%20prosecution%20was%20issued%20only%20on%20April%206%2C%202015.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20well%20before%20the%20sanctioning%20authority%E2%80%99s%20mandatory%20clearance%2C%20the%20trial%20court%20had%20taken%20cognizance%20of%20the%20charges%20against%20Saibaba%2C%20framed%20its%20charges%20and%20even%20gone%20on%20to%20record%20evidence%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndependent%20authority%20did%20not%20apply%20mind%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20other%20five%20persons%2C%20the%20high%20court%20noted%20that%20while%20the%20official%20sanction%20granted%20was%20in%20order%2C%20the%20independent%20authority%E2%80%99s%20report%20which%20preceded%20it%20was%20not.%C2%A0%20The%20independent%20authority%20is%20required%20to%20assess%20the%20material%20evidence%20against%20the%20accused%20persons%20and%20give%20her%20opinion%20before%20the%20sanctioning%20authority%20finally%20grants%20sanction%20for%20prosecution.%20But%20the%20judges%20had%20serious%20objections%20to%20the%20way%20the%20process%20played%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20independent%20authority%20in%20this%20case%20was%20Vidya%20Gundecha%2C%20the%20then%20director%20of%20prosecution.%20The%20high%20court%20pointed%20to%20section%2045(2)%20of%20the%20UAPA%20that%20%E2%80%9Ccreates%20a%20statutory%20bar%20on%20grant%20of%20sanction%20unless%20independent%20authority%20%E2%80%98reviews%E2%80%99%20the%20evidence%20gathered%20and%20gives%20its%20recommendation%20in%20a%20time%20bound%20manner%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CRecommendations%20of%20an%20independent%20authority%20are%20not%20an%20empty%20formality%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20observed.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20however%2C%20Gundecha%20had%20merely%20noted%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20clear%20that%20there%20is%20prima%20facie%20evidence%20against%20the%20arrested%20and%20non-arrested%20accused%20persons%E2%80%A6.%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20recommended%20that%20sanction%20be%20accorded%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECalling%20Gundecha%E2%80%99s%20non-reasoned%20recommendation%20%E2%80%9Ccryptic%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20court%20said%20that%20her%20act%20(or%20lack%20of%20it%20in%20this%20case)%20has%20frustrated%20the%20law%E2%80%99s%20object.%20A%20cryptic%20communication%20cannot%20be%20considered%20a%20%E2%80%9Creport%E2%80%9D%20as%20expected%20under%20the%20law%2C%20the%20judgment%20notes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state%2C%20represented%20by%20senior%20counsel%20Aabad%20Ponda%2C%20had%20argued%20that%20there%20is%20no%20set%20format%20in%20which%20the%20recommendation%20can%20be%20made.%20To%20this%2C%20the%20court%20observed%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CHaving%20regard%20to%20the%20language%20used%20under%20Sub-clause%20(2)%2C%20though%20the%20reasons%20are%20not%20required%2C%20but%20the%20independent%20authority%20is%20certainly%20expected%20to%20at%20least%20communicate%20in%20brief%20as%20to%20what%20prompted%20the%20authority%20to%20make%20the%20recommendation.%20It%20was%20an%20important%20facet%20of%20the%20process%20of%20sanction%20which%20has%20to%20be%20passed%20to%20the%20Sanctioning%20Authority%20to%20enable%20it%20to%20take%20an%20appropriate%20decision.%20We%20do%20agree%20that%20statute%20has%20not%20prescribed%20any%20format%20or%20a%20form%20in%20which%20the%20report%20is%20to%20be%20made.%20However%2C%20it%20was%20the%20minimum%20expectation%20from%20the%20Authority%20that%20the%20report%20would%20convey%20due%20application%20of%20mind.%20The%20very%20purpose%20was%20to%20provide%20assistance%20to%20the%20Sanctioning%20Authority.%20In%20turn%2C%20besides%20a%20go-ahead%20signal%20of%20the%20authority%2C%20there%20is%20nothing%20before%20the%20Sanctioning%20Authority%20for%20its%20consideration%20while%20granting%20sanction.%20As%20such%20the%20legislative%20object%20has%20been%20completely%20frustrated%20by%20said%20communication%20which%20was%20not%20in%20tune%20with%20the%20additional%20filter%20provided%20by%20the%20statute.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESenior%20defence%20counsel%20Subodh%20Dharmadhikari%2C%20who%20appeared%20for%20Saibaba%20in%20the%20high%20court%2C%20pointed%20to%20the%20legal%20history%20of%20the%20UAPA%20and%20the%20amendments%20which%20had%20been%20made%20to%20the%20law.%20Since%20the%20law%20was%20stringent%2C%20Dharmadhikari%20said%20that%20it%20provided%20various%20safeguards%20in%20the%20shape%20of%20power%20to%20arrest%20and%20search.%20He%20argued%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mha.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FA1967-37.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esection%2045%20of%20UAPA%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20unique%20provision%20which%20added%20a%20very%20important%20pre-cognizance%2C%20presanction%20filter%20to%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20sanction%20provision%20goes%20to%20the%20root%20of%20this%20case%2C%20and%20has%20virtually%20raised%20doubts%20over%20the%20entire%20trial%2C%20the%20high%20court%20observed%20that%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20total%20non-compliance%20with%20the%20sanction%20provision%20which%20goes%20to%20the%20very%20root%20of%20the%20case%2C%20vitiating%20everything%20against%20accused%20No.6%20(Saibaba)%20from%20its%20inception%20for%20want%20of%20authority%20of%20the%20trial%20court%20to%20proceed.%20In%20sum%20and%20substance%2C%20the%20prosecution%20against%20accused%20No.6%20G.N.%20Saibaba%20for%20want%20of%20valid%20sanction%20is%20also%20totally%20vitiated.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20defence%20team%20systematically%20built%20its%20argument%20in%20the%20case%2C%20Ponda%20contended%20that%20the%20issue%20of%20sanction%20was%20not%20raised%20by%20the%20defence%20at%20the%20time%20of%20framing%20of%20charges%20or%20at%20other%20important%20stages%20of%20the%20trial%20so%20it%20could%20not%20be%20brought%20up%20now.%20The%20defence%20responded%20by%20bringing%20the%20bail%20application%20filed%20by%20the%20accused%20way%20back%20in%20June%202014%20where%20the%20issue%20of%20sanction%20was%20raised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENot%20simply%20a%20%E2%80%98technical%E2%80%99%20error%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20prosecution%20insisted%20that%20the%20lack%20of%20proper%20sanction%20was%20at%20best%20a%20%E2%80%98technical%E2%80%99%20glitch%20%E2%80%93%20something%20that%20could%20be%20overlooked%20%E2%80%93%20the%20court%20rejected%20this%20argument.%20It%20observed%20that%20while%C2%A0%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F338903%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESection%20465%20of%20the%20Code%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(CrPC)%20does%20allow%20an%20%E2%80%9Cerror%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cirregularity%E2%80%9D%20in%20grant%20of%20sanction%20to%20be%20cured%2C%20it%20%E2%80%9Cdoes%20not%20cover%20omission%20or%20total%20absence%20of%20sanction%E2%80%9D%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20our%20view%2C%20there%20is%20total%20non-compliance%20of%20various%20provisions%20of%20UAPA.%20The%20sanction%20accorded%20to%20prosecute%20Accused%20Nos.1%20to%205%20is%20invalid.%20Taking%20cognizance%20by%20the%20trial%20court%20without%20valid%20sanction%20or%20no%20sanction%20to%20prosecute%20accused%20No.6%20G.N.%20Saibaba%20goes%20to%20the%20root%20of%20the%20case%2C%20which%20renders%20the%20entire%20proceedings%20null%20and%20void%E2%80%A6%20We%20hold%20that%20the%20trial%20held%20despite%20violation%20of%20mandatory%20provisions%20of%20law%20itself%20amounts%20to%20failure%20of%20justice.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20the%20sanction%20aspect%2C%20the%20court%20also%20took%20an%20independent%20look%20at%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20witnesses%20who%20deposed%20in%20the%20case.%20The%20prosecution%20case%20was%20entirely%20built%20on%20the%20statements%20of%2023%20witnesses%2C%20comprising%20only%20police%20personnel%20and%20%3Cem%3Epanch%3C%2Fem%3E%20witnesses.%20The%20court%20also%20looked%20at%20the%20three%20seizures%E2%80%94primarily%20electronic%20evidence%E2%80%94that%20the%20prosecution%20relied%20on%20to%20prove%20its%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20no%20offence%20was%20shown%20to%20be%20committed%20or%20arms%20recovered%20from%20either%20of%20the%20six%20persons%20convicted%20in%20the%20case%2C%20the%20prosecution%20had%20relied%20upon%20section%2043%20(E)%20of%20the%20UAPA%20which%20allows%20%E2%80%9Cpresumption%E2%80%9D%20of%20an%20offence%20to%20be%20committed.%20The%20section%2C%20however%2C%20can%20be%20applied%20only%20if%20the%20accused%20were%20booked%20section%2015%20and%20subsequently%20punished%20under%20section%2016%20(i.e.%20for%20terrorist%20acts)%20or%20found%20to%20be%20in%20possession%20of%20arms%20or%20explosives.%20In%20this%20case%2C%20neither%20were%20arms%20recovered%20nor%20were%20any%20of%20them%20booked%20under%20section%2015%20or%2016%20of%20the%20UAPA.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6In%20criminal%20jurisprudence%2C%20it%20is%20a%20well-recognised%20principle%20that%20the%20onus%20of%20proof%20lies%20on%20the%20prosecution%20and%20is%20higher%20than%20the%20mere%20preponderance%20of%20probability.%20The%20prosecution%20is%20under%20an%20obligation%20to%20establish%20the%20guilt%20of%20the%20accused%20beyond%20reasonable%20doubt%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20observed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EProsecution%20fails%20to%20provide%20evidence%20to%20back%20up%20charges%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20examined%20witness%20statements%20and%20the%20electronic%20evidence%20the%20police%20said%20it%20had%20seized%20but%20came%20to%20the%20conclusion%20that%20the%20prosecution%20had%20failed%20to%20make%20out%20a%20credible%20case.%20Referring%20to%20video%20footage%2C%20for%20example%2C%20the%20court%20noted%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20title%3D%5C%22Page%20286%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CThough%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20electronic%20evidence%20is%20produced%20in%20the%20form%20of%20printed%2Fhard%20copies%20of%20the%20content%20stored%20in%20digital%20form%20or%20in%20the%20nature%20of%20video%20footage%2C%20no%20evidence%20has%20been%20led%20by%20any%20witness%20identifying%20the%20various%20persons%20in%20these%20videos%2C%20or%20deposing%20as%20to%20the%20specific%20statements%20made%20by%20such%20persons%20and%20quoting%20them%2C%20or%20how%20these%20statements%20or%20actions%20in%20videos%20constitute%20material%20to%20make%20out%20an%20offence%20under%20the%20Act.%20Playing%20several%20videos%20or%20requesting%20the%20Court%20to%20read%20through%20hundreds%20of%20pages%20of%20literature%20does%20not%20constitute%20evidence.%20In%20our%20opinion%2C%20there%20should%20have%20been%20specific%20evidence%20led%20through%20witnesses%20to%20connect%20with%20the%20making%20out%20of%20an%20offence.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20any%20depositions%20to%20this%20effect%2C%20we%20are%20afraid%20we%20cannot%20consider%20all%20this%20footage%20to%20be%20evidence.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20title%3D%5C%22Page%20291%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaking%20clear%20that%20the%20decision%20to%20acquit%20Saibaba%20and%20the%20others%20was%20not%20just%20on%20account%20of%20the%20failure%20to%20grant%20sanction%20to%20prosecute%2C%20the%20judgment%20notes%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20prosecution%20has%20failed%20to%20establish%20legal%20arrest%20and%20seizure%20from%20accused%20Nos.1%20to%205%2C%20and%20failed%20to%20establish%20the%20seizure%20of%20incriminating%20material%20from%20the%20house%20search%20of%20accused%20No.6%20G.N.%20Saibaba.%20The%20prosecution%20has%20also%20failed%20to%20prove%20the%20electronic%20evidence%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%20and%20the%20Information%20Technology%20Act.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20title%3D%5C%22Page%20292%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20view%20of%20the%20above%20conclusion%E2%80%9D%2C%20it%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20common%20judgment%20rendered%20by%20the%20Trial%20Court%20%E2%80%A6is%20not%20sustainable%20in%20the%20eyes%20of%20law.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESaibaba%E2%80%99s%20lawyer%20jailed%20in%20Bhima%20Koregaon%20case%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncidentally%2C%20Saibaba%E2%80%99s%20defence%20in%20the%20trial%20court%20was%20handled%20by%20the%20Nagpur-based%20human%20rights%20lawyer%20Surendra%20Gadling%2C%20who%2C%20soon%20after%20the%20completion%20of%20trial%2C%20was%20himself%20arrested%20in%20the%20Elgar%20Parishad%20case.%20Arrested%20on%20June%206%2C%202018%2C%20he%20continues%20to%20be%20incarcerated.%20Gadling%20and%20other%20defence%20lawyers%20in%20the%20Elgar%20Parishad%20case%20have%20said%20that%20he%20was%20targeted%20mainly%20because%20he%20had%20defended%20Saibaba%20in%20the%20trial%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1709671262000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F05%2Fsai2.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsaibaba-acquittal-from-lack-of-sanction-to-dodgy-evidence-high-court-judgment-tears-into-states-case%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'The%20prosecution%20has%20failed%20to%20establish%20the%20seizure%20of%20incriminating%20material%20from%20the%20house%20search%20of%20G.N.%20Saibaba%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judges%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20prosecution%20has%20also%20failed%20to%20prove%20the%20electronic%20evidence%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%20and%20the%20Information%20Techn